medium.description: Primitive. Represents most portrait tablets and moderate desktops with magnification turned on 125+%

large.description: Primitive. Represents most landscape tablets, small desktops, and larger desktops with magnification turned on at 125+%.

xl.description: Primitive. Represents larger tablets and most moderate desktop screen sizes.

2xl.description: Primitive. Represents the majority of large desktop screen sizes.

50.description: Primitive. Used for extra small components â‰¤ 24px such as checkboxes

100.description: Primitive. Used for small components like small buttons, and others with a dimension <40px.

200.description: Primitive. Used for medium or small components like cards, snack bars, banners, buttons, or nested components

300.description: Primitive. Used for large container components like sheets and dialogs

full.description: Primitive. Used for special components such as slider handles, badges, tags and whenever we need a circle.

25.description: Primitive. Used for most of our borders. (e.g. Input Fields, Cards, Menus, Checkboxes, Radios)

300.description: Primitive. Used for our smallest icons

400.description: Primitive. Our default XS width used for interactive components, such as Checkboxes, Radios. Medium icons use this size as well.

600.description: Primitive. Our default small width used for visual components such as large Icons, avatars, and some XS interactive components such as Icon Buttons.

800.description: Primitive. Our default small width used for interactive components with content within them such as Small Icon Buttons

1000.description: Primitive. Our default medium width used for interactive components with content within them such as Icon Buttons
